{"id": 9989, "date": "2019-05-23T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2019-05-23T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=9989"}, "modified": "2024-01-01T18:32:09", "modified_gmt": "2024-01-02T02:32:09", "slug": "cover-me-buckwheat-zydeco-back-in-your-arms", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/05/23/cover-me-buckwheat-zydeco-back-in-your-arms/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me, Buckwheat Zydeco: Back in Your Arms"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>The late, great Buckwheat Zydeco covered one of Bruce&#8217;s more obscure tracks on his final studio album,\u00a0<em>Lay Your Burden Down. </em></p>\n<p>For an artist with a distinct sound of his own, Zydeco&#8217;s version of &#8220;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/11/10/roll-of-the-dice-back-in-your-arms/\">Back in Your Arms</a>&#8221; is surprisingly faithful to the original&#8230; for about thirty seconds. Then Zydeco shifts the song into a reggae arrangement and never looks back.</p>\n<p>Amazingly, it works. I&#8217;d never have imagined Bruce&#8217;s R&amp;B torch song recast as a reggae ballad, but that&#8217;s the wonderful thing about covers: sometimes they deliver surprises that cast new light on an old favorite.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Back In Your Arms\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8LzWJ2XviRc?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One of the last songs Buckwheat Zydeco recorded in the studio was a reggae reinvention of Bruce&#8217;s torch song, &#8220;Back in Your Arms.&#8221; And it works.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 10277, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky"